page_title: Quickstart: Generate images with Azure OpenAI Service using PowerShell
page_description: Learn how to generate images with Azure OpenAI Service by using PowerShell and the endpoint and access keys for your Azure OpenAI resource.
chunk_content: OutputPowerShell requests the image from Azure OpenAI and stores the output image in the _generated_image.png_ file in your specified directory. For convenience, the full path for the file is returned at the end of the script.The image generation APIs come with a content moderation filter. If the service recognizes your prompt as harmful content, it doesn't generate an image. For more information, see Content filtering.
